getting angry again.

22:07.320 --> 22:10.040
I wonder if there's anything about
it in the small print?

22:10.040 --> 22:12.280
Oh, there it is.

22:13.520 --> 22:16.120
In tiny, tiny letters,

22:16.120 --> 22:18.360
<i>"Normal emotions may return if the</i>

22:18.360 --> 22:22.440
<i>patient is reminded of a previous
trauma or hears some bad news".</i>

22:24.560 --> 22:26.200
I'm going out!

22:37.400 --> 22:41.000
So, Jane, I've decided to meet lots
of people in the Colonial later.

22:41.000 --> 22:44.360
I'm going to apologise to every
man Jack and woman Jack

22:44.360 --> 22:46.600
of them individually.

22:46.600 --> 22:48.840
I'm here, Toast.

22:48.840 --> 22:49.920
Oh, yes.

22:52.720 --> 22:54.560
That should cover it. Thanks, Toast.

22:54.560 --> 22:56.000
Sorry for everything, Ian.

22:57.040 --> 22:58.080
Now for this lot.

22:59.680 --> 23:03.280
I say, thank you all for coming.

23:03.280 --> 23:09.560
I owe each one of you a sincere
apology for my anger over the years.

23:11.160 --> 23:13.320
I'm actually getting
quite emotional.

23:13.320 --> 23:15.040
Keep it together, Toast.

23:15.040 --> 23:16.960
You're making a tomfool
of yourself.

23:16.960 --> 23:18.640
Yes, you're right, Blair.

23:18.640 --> 23:21.920
By the way, Toast, you owe me £200.

23:23.320 --> 23:27.560
Well, I've given all my cash to Ian,
to pay my bar tab.

23:27.560 --> 23:29.680
Bar tab?!

23:29.680 --> 23:32.960
Toast, the only reason all of us
are here tonight

23:32.960 --> 23:35.960
in this bugger house is
because we thought you

23:35.960 --> 23:38.000
were going to repay our loans.

23:38.000 --> 23:41.120
That's the only reason we're here.

23:42.680 --> 23:44.120
Now, what say you, sir?

23:51.000 --> 23:52.040
Good Lord.

23:54.080 --> 23:55.360
You'll be lucky.

23:55.360 --> 23:57.360
By my reckoning,

23:57.360 --> 24:01.840
I'd say I'm the only man in this
room that owes you, Toast.

24:01.840 --> 24:03.320
This.

24:03.320 --> 24:05.520
It's for making love to my wife

24:05.520 --> 24:06.880
in my bed,

24:06.880 --> 24:08.960
sometimes when I was in the house,

24:08.960 --> 24:11.800
actually, sometimes
even when I was in the bed!

24:11.800 --> 24:13.280
For the last 20...

24:16.200 --> 24:18.880
Oh, yeah! Come on, Purchase,
ruck in there!

24:18.880 --> 24:19.920
Knock him out!

24:22.600 --> 24:24.520
What have you got, Toast?

24:24.520 --> 24:25.680
Oh, my goodness.

24:29.520 --> 24:30.560
Purchase!

24:32.040 --> 24:33.360
Come on, Purchase!

24:37.920 --> 24:40.880
All right, gentlemen,
£20 on the man in the moustache.

24:59.400 --> 25:01.000
God, not in the knackers.

25:05.000 --> 25:07.360
Oh, my giddy Aunt Sally!

25:07.360 --> 25:09.640
That'll teach you,
Ray bloody Purchase.

25:12.200 --> 25:13.560
Champagne, sir?

25:13.560 --> 25:16.320
It's an 1841 Veuve Clicquot.

25:16.320 --> 25:17.720
I'll bet it is!

25:17.720 --> 25:19.160
There you go, sir.

25:23.640 --> 25:26.200
Jane? I'm safely on the plane.

25:26.200 --> 25:28.840
Away from the baying mob.

25:28.840 --> 25:31.480
Can you believe they only turned up
to collect money off me?

25:31.480 --> 25:33.840
Ha! Saved in the nick of time.

25:33.840 --> 25:36.920
Now, let me give you some more
details about the terrific

25:36.920 --> 25:38.800
stroke of luck you've had.

25:38.800 --> 25:41.080
With Purchase now
out of the picture,

25:41.080 --> 25:44.280
I immediately contacted Doubledecker
to say you were still

25:44.280 --> 25:45.520
very much available.

25:45.520 --> 25:48.800
He said yes immediately,
they're even paying for your flight.

25:48.800 --> 25:52.680
Ha! Thank God for Doubledecker.
<i>DOOB-ledecker.</i>

25:52.680 --> 25:57.120
And hooray for Hollywood,
you're going to Tinseltown, Toast.

25:57.120 --> 25:58.720
Can you believe it?

25:58.720 --> 26:00.320
How's Ray Purchase?

26:00.320 --> 26:02.240
Two broken legs
and a badly sprained neck,

26:02.240 --> 26:03.840
he'll be out of action for months.

26:03.840 --> 26:06.680
Two broken legs, fantastic!

26:06.680 --> 26:10.840
Everything's worked out dandy,
Jane, just dandy.

26:10.840 --> 26:12.920
Have a nice day! Ha!

26:12.920 --> 26:17.680
I almost forgot, what's the name of
the movie that I'm going to be in?

26:17.680 --> 26:19.800
The latest Star Wars movie.

26:19.800 --> 26:23.160
You've heard of the Star Wars,
I take it?

26:23.160 --> 26:24.920
Yes, Jane,

26:24.920 --> 26:27.160
even I've heard Star Wars.

26:27.160 --> 26:29.840
Excuse me, buddy?
I think you're in my seat.

26:32.240 --> 26:33.920
Oh, yes.

26:33.920 --> 26:35.040
Apologies, old chap.

26:38.840 --> 26:40.240
Toast.

26:40.240 --> 26:42.600
Steven Toast.

26:42.600 --> 26:44.520
I'm Nightlife.

26:44.520 --> 26:46.440
Russ Nightlife.

26:46.440 --> 26:47.800
Pleased to meet you.
